textBeforeTable: Schedule: In the Czech Extraleague the regular season ends with a busy game day. It all starts on Friday with a derby between the Eagles Prague and the Tempo Titans Prague. Four doubleheaders follow on Saturday before three single games close out the last preliminary phase game day. Draci Brno already has secured first place with a 27-5 record. They are followed by Kotlarka Prague (22-10), Arrows Ostrava (18-14), Technika Brno (15-17), Eagles Prague (14-18), Tempo Titans (13-19), Hrosi Brno (10-22) and Skokani Olomouc (9-23).
